item.title: -.-! Identifier Expected
item.dc:creator: @Nashi Nashi
item.description:
@Nashi wrote:

[scar]//\Emma’s AutoFletcher!//\

program AutoFletcher;
{
Have a knife ANYwhere but last spot in your inventory! =D
}
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}

var
BankExitCross, UseQuck : integer;

procedure bitmap;
begin
BankExitCross := BitmapFromString(21, 21, ‘z78DACD96510E832’ +
‘00C40AF046D29F02932EE7FA419BB0F1606763A32FD783169CB2B’ +
‘011B8DD91E6BFECA98A3F5EB8B361097190CEC13076FD812D7F66’ +
‘49710E33C7BED75C501AEEDDE253A8F2E52C6E88822FA37FBDEE1’ +
‘6C3B3DC8210A5B3B2797096BD6396DF4DBFC2BF6710F9ACC9E5D6’ +
‘EC5B995F51D1ED8C979B23D6ABEDCF10A57ECE31E34B5DB5D2F50’ +
‘84E7EC6D0FFA2A424C9084AD5DE6C098BDBD6B6AAFD835E77ECEB’ +
‘ECDB96D14E9BDFAE817769984153FACDCE4E833AFD87B5E7DFE81’ +
‘7D9FFFF3880B02B0F04676647634DD4E90015ABB44E544EA0E7FC’ +
‘6DD0B09D866793737F8A37B02401A2273’);

UseQuck := CreateBitmapMaskFromText(‘Use-quickly’, Upchars); //or ‘uickly’ if that doesnt work

end;

procedure getlogs;
begin
if(findcolortolerance(x,y,5593184,290,150,310,170,20)) then
begin
movemousesmooth(x,y);
wait(100 + random(199));
clickmouse(x + random(10),y + random(5),false);
wait(300 + random(100));
if(FindBitmapToleranceIn(UseQuck,x,y,0,0,700,700,100)) then
begin
movemousesmooth(x,y);
wait(100 + random(100));
clickmouse(x,y + random(1),true);
end;
end;
end;

Begin
SetUpSRL;
end.[/scar]

You Don’t need to declare x and y as integers if your using SRL, Also you need a . before include(.include), And instead of using a whole bitmap We just used CreateBitmapMaskFromText. If it doesnt work just tell me and ill help
